Business Brief -- RBW Corp.:
   Loan-Accord Default Leads
   To Lenders' Negotiations
RBW said its bank lenders agreed to extend their loan
agreements on an interim basis, but have limited borrowing to
$15.5 million. Met Life agreed to defer its $1.8 million
principal payment, due Feb. 15, through the end of the month.
   The company also said it is negotiating with financial
advisers who will assist RBW in finding ways to improve
shareholder value and operating results, and in gathering
future capital.
   An investor group including Glen F. Ceiley of Bisco
Industries Inc. has been trying to acquire RBW.